In [[aerospace]], '''Assembly, Test, and Launch Operations''' ('''ATLO'''), also known as Mission System Integration and Test (MSIT) is the phase of a spacecraft project that comprises building the spacecraft, testing it, and getting it launched.<ref>{{cite book|title=ROVING MARS: SPIRIT, OPPORTUNITY, AND THE EXPLORATION OF THE RED PLANET|author=Steven W. Squyres|pages=142|year=2005|publisher=Hyperion|isbn=1-4013-0149-5}}</ref>

