UNESP ranked in the 151-200th group of the Young University Rankings 2018 and in the 601-800th group of the World University Rankings 2018 by THE.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/world-university-rankings/sao-paulo-state-university-unesp|title=São Paulo State University (UNESP)|website=Times Higher Education (THE)|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
== Research == {{Expand section|date=August 2018}} Research an UNESP is centrally organized by the Research Vice-President's office (PROPe).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www2.unesp.br/portal#!/international/research|title=Unesp - Universidade Estadual Paulista - Portal|website=www2.unesp.br|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref> The university currently has its main research focus in the areas of [[Bioenergy]], [[Biotechnology]], [[Climate change|Climate Change]], [[Nanotechnology]], [[Pharmacology|Pharmaceutical Development and Technology]], [[Pre-clinical development|Pre-Clinical]] and [[Drug development|Clinical development]], [[Public policy|Public Policy]], Sea Sciences and [[Stem-cell research|Stem Cell]] research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www2.unesp.br/portal#!/international/research/strategic-areas|title=Unesp - Universidade Estadual Paulista - Portal|website=www2.unesp.br|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
In 2010, [[UNESCO]], an agency of the [[United Nations]] (UN), named UNESP as the 2nd university in Brazil in numbers of scientific articles of international level, being responsible for 8% of the national scientific production, alongside [[Unicamp|UNICAMP]] and second to [[University of São Paulo|USP.]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.planetauniversitario.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=18421:unesco-aponta-unesp-em-segundo-lugar-no-brasil-em-producao-cientifica&catid=27:notas-do-campus&Itemid=73|title=Unesco aponta Unesp em segundo lugar no Brasil em produção científica|website=www.planetauniversitario.com|language=pt-br|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref> Other sources state that UNESP is accounting for 25% of total high-quality scientific publications in Brazil.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omicsonline.org/universities/Sao_Paulo_State_University/|title=Sao Paulo State University|website=www.omicsonline.org|access-date=2018-08-15}}</ref>
